	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				I think most people are missing the point between 1HS and 2HS. The difference in damage is neglegable when compared to the effects. <BR>
<BR>
1HS opts for speed over power.<BR>
2HS opts for power over speed. <BR>
<BR>
Everyone knows this. However, if you actually APPLY that knowledge, than you will be much better off. <BR>
<BR>
Use 2HS to inflict High Damage when it is needed in a melee situation. I would much rather be hacking away at a strictly melee creature with a 2HS. Maximizing my damage.<BR>
<BR>
Use 1HS when fighting casters. Your chances of interrupting their casting is greatly increased when combined with bash (yes bash, not Kick!!!). Of course, pierce works nicely for this too. The object here is to keep the MoB busy while your casters inflict most of the damage.<BR>
<BR>
My warrior uses both. However, he does NOT use a shield. I have hotkeyed my primary and secondary weapon slot, as well as the bottom two primary slots in my inventory. This allows me switch between 2 1HS and 1 2HS.<BR>
I could even supliment with a shield if I had too.<BR>
<BR>
<BR>
<BR>
No one skill outweighs another. However, certain situations do allow one to shine over the other. A good player knows this and prepares for it (In fact, think of everytime you have died. 9 times out of 10, it was from lack of preparation!!!)<BR>
<BR>
As allways, Good hunting
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
